(17, 1, 1, 'Best Time To Visit Hoi An ‚Äì Crafting Your Perfect Itinerary For Hoi An', 'Best Time To Visit Hoi An ‚Äì Crafting Your Perfect Itinerary For Hoi An', 'Arriving in Hoi An in a stunning classic, we learned that this city offers the greatest experiences that anyone should have at least once in their lifetime. Watch the best things to do in Hoi An that meet the expectations of both domestic and foreign visitors here.', '<h3 id=\"1\">1. Hoi An in Vietnam &ndash; Why do many tourists love Hoian so much?</h3>\r\n<p>Hoi An, a busy port in Central Vietnam, was founded in the sixteenth century. Hoi An is a crossroads for several cultures, including Vietnamese, Chinese, Japanese, Dutch, and Portuguese. As a result, Hoi An has evolved its own culture. There are numerous reasons why people love to visit Hoi An.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Ancient architecture:</strong>&nbsp;Hoi An historic Town is a collection of historic architectural artifacts from several cultures. Hoi An architectural works are constructed using traditional materials such as wood, brick, stone, and so on, as well as innovative building techniques</li>\r\n<li><strong>Distinct culture:</strong>&nbsp;Hoi An is a city steeped in traditional Vietnamese culture. Visitors to Hoi An can participate in a variety of distinctive cultural activities, including the lantern festival, the Lim festival, and so on.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Diverse cuisine:</strong>&nbsp;This city is a culinary wonderland, featuring several delectable and appealing cuisines. Cao Lau, Hoi An bread, Quang noodles, Hoi An chicken rice, and other unique meals are available in Hoi An.</li>\r\n<li><strong>The pricing is affordable:</strong>&nbsp;Here is a low-cost tourist resort that appeals to a wide range of visitors. Finally, Hoi An is a peaceful, poetic city, giving visitors a feeling of relaxation and comfort.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/things-to-do-in-hoian.jpg\" alt=\"things to do in hoian\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"2\">2. Hoi An weather by month</h3>\r\n<p>Hoi An, like many other provinces in the central region, suffers annually from many natural disasters such as storms, floods, etc., causing damage to people as well as tourism. We hope you will have a specific and clear plan for your upcoming trip. The Hoi An weather-by-month and also Hoi An temperature by month information is provided below to help you in making a plan for the trip.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.1\">2.1 January</h4>\r\n<p>The dry season begins in Hoi An in January, so visitors will enjoy the nice environment of the old town. The temperature in Hoi An at this time of year normally ranges between 18&deg;C (64&deg;F) and 23&deg;C (73&deg;F), bringing cool and chilly weather for visitors to feel more at ease with their trips.The weather in Hoi An by month is shown below.</p>\r\n<p>This time of year, in particular, is when the inhabitants of Hoi An are busy preparing for the Lunar New Year holiday. As a result, if you are fortunate enough to visit on this occasion, you will be able to immerse yourself in the incredibly hectic and bright atmosphere to enjoy the lantern festival, a traditional cultural symbol of the old town</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/best-time-to-visit-hoian.jpg\" alt=\"Best time to visit Hoian\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.2\">2.2 February</h4>\r\n<p>The month of February is great for exploring the transformation of a rustic, unpretentious, and inviting city into a tourist magnet with a wide range of intriguing entertainment activities. Because the weather in Hoi An is so good at this time of year, with little rain, dry weather, and an average temperature ranging from 26&deg;C (78&deg;F) to 28&deg;C (82&deg;F), it is great for sightseeing, exploration, and entertainment activities.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.3\">2.3 March</h4>\r\n<p>The weather in March, like the first two months of the year, is perfect during the year when the temperature is constant, the weather is cool and pleasant, and there is no rain. When visiting Hoi An in March, you can engage in a variety of thrilling fun and discovery activities such as sunbathing on the beach, riding a water motorbike, surfing, and attending the temple ritual at the start of the year&hellip; At this time, the old town is also busy. Everyone wants to be immersed in that fascinating place when they wear a vivid shirt full of vitality. This is the best month to visit&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/things-to-do-in-hoi-an-vietnam/\">Hoi An Vietnam</a></p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoi-an-at-night.jpg\" alt=\"Best time to visit Hoi An\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.4\">2.4 April</h4>\r\n<p>April marks the transition from spring to summer, and Hoi An is dressed in a bright, dazzling yellow shirt. During the day, the average temperature is between 24? (75?) and 25&deg;C (77&deg;F). Hoi An&rsquo;s lovely weather and fresh, crisp air will make every tourist nostalgic. If you are concerned about unexpected rains on your vacation to discover Hoi An tourism, April is the best month to visit. Hoi An&rsquo;s million check-in places and authentic virtual living will captivate visitors. Rows of antique houses, beautiful yellow walls, poetic lantern streets, and so on have all become popular hangouts for visitors.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.5\">2.5 May</h4>\r\n<p>Traveling to Hoi An in May allows guests to fully appreciate the old and romantic charm of Hoi An. Furthermore, the weather in May is particularly good, making it ideal for any exploratory journeys. May is the dry season in Hoi An, so the weather is sunny with minimal rain, and the temperature ranges from 26&deg;C (78&deg;F) to 31&deg;C (87&deg;F), making it extremely nice. This time of year, the weather is perfect: bright but not too hot, with plentiful travel services and breathtaking landscapes ideal for creating virtual check-in images.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/walking-hoi-an-ancient-town.jpg\" alt=\"Best time to visit Hoi An in may\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.6\">2.6 June</h4>\r\n<p>When visiting Hoi An in June, the temperature is slightly warmer than in previous months, but there are many exciting experiences that are characterized by &ldquo;summer,&rdquo; the biggest tourist season of the year. The temperature in Hoi An at this time of year is slightly higher than in the first months of the year, ranging from 26&deg;C (78&deg;F) to 36&deg;C (96&deg;F). Although June does not have the best weather of the year, Hoi An is constantly welcoming many people to visit and experience the distinctive atmosphere of Hoi An at any time of the year.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.7\">2.7 July</h4>\r\n<p>In July, the weather in Hoi An will be generally good for travelers. The average daily temperature ranges from 26&deg;C (78&deg;F) to 27&deg;C (80&deg;F), with high temperatures reaching 28 to 33 &deg;C. Rainfall is light, ranging from 3mm to 6mm. The average humidity ranges from 50% to 65%, which is fairly low. Hoi An is not too hot in the early mornings or late afternoons due to the aforesaid weather conditions, making it extremely convenient to travel, explore magnificent places, and participate in leisure sports and sports activities. Outdoor activity. Tourists can travel to Hoi An with confidence and comfort during the most beautiful month of the year, July.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoi-an-in-vietnam.jpg\" alt=\"hoian vietnam\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.8\">2.8 August</h4>\r\n<p>In August, Hoi An begins the rainy season, and the weather is cool and pleasant. However, at this time, there is not much rain, which does not affect the travel and sightseeing journeys of tourists. Traveling to Hoi An in August has many advantages, such as:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The number of visitors is too large; visitors will be able to freely play and admire the scenery without having to jostle or push.</li>\r\n<li>Hoi An has a distinct, serene, poetic, and romantic beauty during the rainy season.</li>\r\n<li>Visitors can float in a boat to discover the beauty of Hoi An ancient town in flood water if they arrive during heavy rain.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.9\">2.9 September</h4>\r\n<p>In September, the weather in Hoi An, as well as many other destinations in Quang Nam province, begins to be influenced by the rainy season. However, this place is still subject to the heat of the dry season, so the temperature is quite high, averaging about 23&deg;C (73&deg;F) to 30&deg;C (86&deg;F). In September, the natural scenery in Hoi An becomes especially beautiful and poetic. dreamy and lyrical. These days, when the golden sunlight shines down, the old streets and old houses will be filled with warm light, creating a colorful and romantic space. September is also the ideal time to travel to Hoi An, which will bring you memorable and surprising experiences.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-countryside.jpg\" alt=\"best time visit hoian\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.10\">2.10 October</h4>\r\n<p>Traveling to Hoi An in October allows visitors to see the city&rsquo;s calm, nostalgic beauty at its best. The rain falls on the street, as does the historic, peaceful charm of Hoi An. Hoi An is innately like this. Years have gone, and the splendor of this location has faded, but the ancient beauty remains in this calm Hoi An town near to the Hoai River. People&rsquo;s hearts are no less sorrowful when it rains for a long time, yet when they arrive in Hoi An, they will feel strangely familiar. At this time, the highest temperature during the day ranges from about 28&deg;C to 30&deg;C, with many times the temperature dropping lower than about 26&deg;C (78&deg;F) or even up to about 32&deg;C (89&deg;F)</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.11\">2.11 November</h4>\r\n<p>Hoi An in November has its own characteristics, different from other times of the year. This is the time of year when Hoi An has rainy, chilly weather. Traveling to Hoi An in November will bring you a memorable and extremely interesting trip. Even though this place has been famous for many years, it has never lost any of its charm. At that time, although it was the rainy season, the beauty of Hoi An appeared extremely attractive, with charm and poetry, making it very worth admiring. Under the gentle rain, the street will become quiet and not crowded and noisy like during peak tourist seasons. You will comfortably explore every corner of Hoi An in the most carefree way.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.12\">2.12 December</h4>\r\n<p>Coming to Hoi An in December, you will be able to enjoy the fresh climate, wander into some delicious restaurants to enjoy specialties, and then slowly visit famous tourist attractions in Hoi An. Hoi An&rsquo;s weather in December is extremely ideal for you to travel around the old town. The temperature in Hoi An at this time is about 19&deg;C (66&deg;F)&ndash;27&deg;C (68&deg;F), which is moderate and pleasant. It is cool during the day and a bit chilly in the evening. On the coldest days, the temperature can drop below 20&deg;C (80&deg;F) degrees Celsius.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-lantern-market.jpg\" alt=\"weather in hoian vietnam \"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"3\">3. Best time to visit Hoi An Vietnam</h3>\r\n<p>We have just told you about the weather in Hoi An during the months of the year. If the above information is still making you wonder what time to come to Hoi An, below we will tell you the best time to travel Hoi An.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.1\">3.1 Dry Season</h4>\r\n<p>The dry season in Hoi An starts from February to August. The average temperature here is about 33&deg;C (91&deg;F); the weather is sunny and clear, and only a few cool showers are scattered in early summer. Traveling to Hoi An in the dry season will be suitable for outdoor activities, sightseeing, photography, fun, and cultural and culinary experiences. The dry weather in the dry season will make traveling, sightseeing, and eating more convenient. The dry season is the time when many unique programs and festivals take place in Hoi An, bringing you many interesting experiences.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/paper-lantern.jpg\" alt=\"paper lantern - best things to do in hoi an\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.2\">3.2 Wet Season</h4>\r\n<p>In Hoi An, the wet season runs from September to January of the next year. But the rain in Hoi An is also fairly mild, which makes for wonderfully romantic moments. This is the best time to visit Hoi An if you&rsquo;re a quiet traveler who prefers a journey that&rsquo;s not too busy or noisy. During the rainy season, the old town has a serene, lyrical, and beautiful charm. You can pleasantly visit without feeling cramped into the stifling atmosphere when there aren&rsquo;t too many people around. Seeing Hoi An during floods, in particular, offers a unique perspective on the old town&rsquo;s splendor</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/enjoy-Hoi-An-old-town.jpg\" alt=\"enjoy Hoi An old town\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"4\">4. How many days to spend in Hoi An?</h3>\r\n<p>Spend at least two days and one night in Hoi An to truly appreciate its splendor! We hope that the itinerary below will enable you and your family have the most enjoyable trip possible:</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"4.1\"><strong>Day 1</strong></h4>\r\n<p><strong>Morning:</strong>&nbsp;Because you must travel frequently, you can arrange your luggage, shower, and rest after arriving in Hoi An and checking into your hotel.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Afternoon:</strong>&nbsp;You and your family can travel and explore Hoi An, a historic town, after savoring specialties at local restaurants.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Check-in at Cau Pagoda:</strong>&nbsp;This pagoda is considered the soul of the old town, with architecture imbued with Japanese breath that is extremely unique and impressive.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Enjoy Mot Hoi An tea,</strong>&nbsp;a well-known, tasty, and aromatic herbal tea produced according to an old-town recipe.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Evening:</strong>&nbsp;Cruise down the Hoai River at night to see the splendor of Hoi An and visit the Night Market in Hoi An. Let us all light fire lanterns to wish the family peace and happiness. To learn more about the significance of releasing flower lanterns into the river, visit Things to Do in Hoi An.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Japanese-Covered-Bridge.jpg\" alt=\"Da nang to Hoi An\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"4.2\"><strong>Day 2</strong></h4>\r\n<p><strong>Morning:</strong>&nbsp;In Hoi An, see two classic antique works</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Tan Ky ancient home</strong>&nbsp;has the architecture of three cultures: Japan, China, and Vietnam, and it houses numerous valuable antiques. They include significant insights about human life</li>\r\n<li><strong>Fujian Assembly Hall</strong>&nbsp;is a popular spiritual tourist site for Fujian people in Hoi An in particular, as well as travelers from all over the world.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Afternoon:</strong>&nbsp;Take a bicycle tour to the countryside.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Explore the coconut village of Cam Thanh:</strong>&nbsp;This community specializes in traditional coconut painting crafts. The coexistence of the coconut painting technique and the ecosystem of the Cam Thanh nipa palm forest has produced a cultural space in which domestic and foreign tourists can learn and participate.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Visit craft villages:</strong>&nbsp;Every artisan village is unique in its beauty, featuring a wide range of jobs from bronze casting to handicraft creations like silk and feather lamps. Additionally, guests can explore creating handicrafts under the supervision of an expert. You should definitely give this experience a try.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-coconut-village.jpg\" alt=\"cam thanh coconut village\"></div>\r\n<h4><strong>Join a day trip to Da Nang from Hoi An:</strong></h4>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/tours/da-nang-city-tour-deluxe-group/\"><strong>Join Day Trip to Da Nang from Hoi An</strong></a>&nbsp;is an ideal choice to explore the dynamic beach city with a perfect itinerary via famous attractions, including historical and cultural landmarks, high-quality cars, and an authentic local tour guide.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/da-nang-to-hoi-an.jpg\" alt=\"day trip to Da Nang from Hoi An\"></div>\r\n<h4><strong>Explore Hue Day Trip from Hoi An:</strong></h4>\r\n<p>If you have visited Da Nang and Hoi An, don&rsquo;t forget to visit Hue city, a dreamy, peaceful city with many ancient and long-preserved buildings. Coming to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/hoi-an-tours/hoi-an-hue-hoi-an-tour/\"><strong>Hue Day Trip from Hoi An</strong></a>, you will have the opportunity to visit works from the Nguyen Dynasty, as well as the architectural features of royal tombs. Spiritual tourism is also a place not to be missed when visiting Hue.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/join-hue-city-tour-from-hoian.jpg\" alt=\"Hue to Hoi An\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"5\">5. How to get to Hoi An?</h3>\r\n<h4 id=\"5.1\">5.1 How to travel to Hoi An</h4>\r\n<p>Getting to Hoi An from abroad can go well and be a fun experience if you take these important steps:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Visa Requirements: Check the visa requirements for Vietnam before booking your journey. Many nationalities are exempt from visa requirements or can receive a visa on arrival. Our post contains all of the necessary information on E-Visa in Vietnam.</li>\r\n<li>The flight arrives at Da Nang International Airport, then takes the bus to Hoi An: You may get to Hoi An by flying to Da Nang International Airport and then taking a taxi or a bus from there. If you enjoy the thrill of exploration, you can hire a private automobile to take you from Da Nang to Hoi An.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 id=\"5.2\">5.2 How to get around Hoi An</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Join Hoi An Day Trip from Da Nang:</strong>&nbsp;If you are traveling around Danang, just about 60km from Hoi An Old Town, you can consider a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/tours/day-trip-to-hoi-an-from-da-nang/\"><strong>Hoi An Day Trip from Da Nang &ndash; Private Tour</strong></a>&nbsp;to explore the ancient beauty of the old town with your loved ones in your own group. Another ideal choice you can add to your list of things to do in Hoi An is to be a part of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/tours/day-trip-from-da-nang-to-hoi-an/\"><strong>Hoi An Day Trip from Da Nang &ndash; Deluxe Group Tour</strong></a>. This option will be perfect if you want to discover every little corner of the old town with other travelers who share a common love with Hoi An, especially with a friendly-budget.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Private Cars:</strong>&nbsp;Booking a private car in advance is a fantastic choice if you prefer a flexible vacation that fits your preferences and timetable. To enjoy a safe ride and talk with our English-speaking driver, book your vacation with our Vietnam Car Rental.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Taxis or Grabs:</strong>&nbsp;Grab, Be, GoJek, and, more recently, Xanh SM are popular ride-hailing apps in Vietnam, allowing you to book economical rides across the city. Traditional taxis are also available, and trustworthy metered firms should be used.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Renting a Motorbike:</strong>&nbsp;Renting a motorbike is a popular way for adventurers to explore Hoi An and its surrounds. Please wear a helmet, carry identification, and obey local traffic laws.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Tra-Que-Village.jpg\" alt=\"Hue to Hoi An\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"6\">6. Is Hoi An worth visiting?</h3>\r\n<p>Is Hoi An worth visiting? When visiting Vietnam, a lot of visitors ask us this question. Travelers visiting Hoi An will surely be captivated by its unique architecture, rich and varied cuisine, long history, and strategic placement at the nexus of multiple cultures from across the globe.</p>\r\n<p>Hoi An consistently preserves its quiet, serene, and uncomplicated qualities. On your next vacation, you and your family shouldn&rsquo;t miss this location. Check out Things to Do in Hoi An to find out more about this city and whether it&rsquo;s worth visiting.</p>\r\n<p><em>In conclusion, come to Hoi An during the dry season to have experiences, appreciate distinctive cultural elements, and participate in festivals with the locals. You will not be disappointed by Hoi An. All essential information regarding the Hoi An Tour is provided below.</em></p>', 'posts/January2024/6dA57V5X1LyuQFSt8YpI.png', 'best-time-to-visit-hoi-an-crafting-your-perfect-itinerary-for-hoi-an', 'Arriving in Hoi An in a stunning classic, we learned that this city offers the greatest experiences that anyone should have at least once in their lifetime. Watch the best things to do in Hoi An that meet the expectations of both domestic and foreign visitors here.', 'Best Time To Visit Hoi An ‚Äì Crafting Your Perfect Itinerary For Hoi An', 'PUBLISHED', 1, '2023-12-28 21:17:35', '2024-01-17 02:26:23'),
(18, 1, 1, 'Hoi An Night Market ‚Äì Street Food & Lots Of Shopping 2024', 'Hoi An Night Market ‚Äì Street Food & Lots Of Shopping 2024', 'This place is known for its lively and festive atmosphere. You will see many beautifully lit up with colorful lanterns that add to the charm of the old town. It is a great time for relaxation in the riverside setting that enhances the experience. Let‚Äôs explore what to do in this night market right below.', '<h3 id=\"1\">1. Night Market in Hoi An</h3>\r\n<p>The market is situated along the riverside in the heart of Hoi An&rsquo;s Old Town. You can find 2-night markets to stay opposite the Hoai River, Nguyen Hoang Street, Hoian, and the other one at Cong Nu Ngoc Hoa Street.</p>\r\n<p>This is an area that attracts many tourists when visiting Hoi An. You not only enjoy Hoian&rsquo;s specialty dishes but also buy many famous things from this place, in addition to dining activities, and shopping, you also choose a corner and take a cooktail with live music. This is truly a place not to be missed when Hoian lights up.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/nguyen-hoang-night-market.jpg\" alt=\"hoi an night markets\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.1\">1.1 Hoi An Night Market Tickets.</h4>\r\n<p>There is typically no entrance fee or tickets required to enter this Night Market. It&rsquo;s a public space, and visitors can freely explore the market area, shop, and enjoy the atmosphere without any admission cost.</p>\r\n<p>However, it&rsquo;s important to note that circumstances can change, and it&rsquo;s advisable to check for the latest information or any updates regarding entrance fees, if applicable, from local sources or travel companies.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"1.2\">1.2 Best Time To Visit Hoi An Night Market?</h4>\r\n<p>As Hoi An night market opening hours, the Night Market usually opens in the early evening and remains operational until late at night.The exact opening hours may vary depending on the seasons of the year, in summer they will open from 18:00 to 22:00, even 23:00. In the winter, it will open from 18:00 to 21:00 or 22:00 pm.</p>\r\n<p>If you come in the early evening, you will catch the moment the old town transitions from daylight to the beautifully lit evening atmosphere.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/markets-in-hoi-an-vietnam-1.jpg\" alt=\"Best Time To Visit Hoi An Night Market\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"2\">2. Location of Hoi An Night Market.</h3>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.1\">2.1 Nguyen Hoang Night Market (Souvenirs and Handicrafts).</h4>\r\n<p>You can find items like lanterns, silk products, traditional textiles, souvenirs, handicrafts, clothing, and other traditional Vietnamese goods in this market with many different types.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/nguyen-hoang-night-market.jpg\" alt=\"Best Time To Visit Hoi An Night Market\"></div>\r\n<p>Location: Nguyen Hoang Street, An Hoi Islet, Hoi An.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.2\">2.2 Cong Nu Ngoc Hoa Food Night Market.</h4>\r\n<p>Location: Cong Nu Ngoc Hoa Street, and Bach Dang Street, Hoi An,</p>\r\n<p>This area is famous for its diverse range of Vietnamese street food. It&rsquo;s a great place to explore local culinary delights, from traditional dishes to snacks and desserts. The food market is a key highlight for those looking to experience Vietnamese cuisine in a lively and bustling atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p>If you don&rsquo;t know where to try the best local food in Hoi An, the night market is a good place for you to try. You can try Quang noodles, Cao Lau, sweet soup, white rose cake, rice cake bake&hellip;</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-at-night.jpg\" alt=\"Cong Nu Ngoc Hoa Food Night Market\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"3\">3. Top Things To Do In Hoi An Night Market.</h3>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.1\">3.1 Experience Vietnamese cuisine at Hoi An food markets.</h4>\r\n<p>Cong Nu Ngoc Hoa Food Night Market: Try a variety of Vietnamese street food and local specialties. From savory dishes like pho (noodle soup) to sweet treats like b&aacute;nh x&egrave;o (Vietnamese pancake) to banh mi (Vietnamese sandwich), the food market is a delight for food enthusiasts.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.2\">3.2 Shopping At Traditional Stores.</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Handicraft Products:</strong>&nbsp;Explore stalls and shops offering a wide range of Vietnamese handicrafts, including intricately crafted items such as lacquerware, wood carvings, and embroidered textiles.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Conical Hats:</strong>&nbsp;Purchase traditional non la (conical hats), an iconic Vietnamese symbol. These hats are not only practical for sun protection but also make for unique and culturally significant souvenirs.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Clothes:</strong>&nbsp;Hoi An is renowned for its tailor shops. Consider getting custom-made clothing, including traditional ao dai (Vietnamese traditional dress) or modern outfits tailored to your preferences.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Straw Bags:</strong>&nbsp;Find stylish and locally made straw bags, a popular accessory among tourists and locals alike.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Bamboo and Ceramic Items:</strong>&nbsp;Discover handcrafted bamboo products and intricate ceramics. Bamboo items may include baskets, trays, and household goods, while ceramic products often showcase the region&rsquo;s traditional pottery.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Coffee:</strong>&nbsp;some types of Vietnam coffee you must try, are egg hot coffee, salt coffee, coconut coffee, and durian coffee, which are great taste.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Lanterns:</strong>&nbsp;Hoi An is famous for its beautifully crafted lanterns. You can find many types of lanterns with different sizes, colors, and shapes. These lanterns are not only decorative but also make for wonderful keepsakes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Tailor-Made-Clothes-1.jpg\" alt=\"Cong Nu Ngoc Hoa Food Night Market\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.3\">3.3 Take a Boat Trip on the Hoai River.</h4>\r\n<p>Enjoy a peaceful boat ride along the Hoai River, especially during the evening when the market is illuminated. This offers a unique perspective of Hoi An&rsquo;s architecture and the vibrant atmosphere along the riverbanks.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.4\">3.4 Send your wishes into the flower lantern.</h4>\r\n<p>If you have a wish for your family or for your lovey relates, you can whisper in the paper lantern and drop it on the river, the lantern will help you bring your wish to the horizon line and make it come true. You can consider the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/hoi-an-lantern-festival/\"><strong>Hoi An Lantern Festival 2024</strong></a>&nbsp;itinerary overview to prepare for the perfect trip!</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoi-an-river-lantern.jpg\" alt=\"Take a Boat Trip on the Hoai River.\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.5\">3.5 Play Bai Choi.</h4>\r\n<p>Bai Choi is a traditional Vietnamese game that combines elements of music, poetry, and acting. It&rsquo;s a popular activity at festivals and events. If there&rsquo;s a Bai Choi session happening at the night market, join in for a fun and cultural experience.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.6\">3.6 Enjoy Live Music at the Restaurant in the Night Market.</h4>\r\n<p>Many restaurants in the Hoi An Night Market feature live music performances, providing a pleasant backdrop to your dining experience. Let&rsquo;s take a cocktail and listen to your favorite song.</p>\r\n<p><strong>And we highly recommend some restaurants below:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Tiger Tiger Bar, 35 Nguyen Phuc Chu, Minh An Ward, Hoi An, Vietnam</li>\r\n<li>The Shamrock Irish Pub Hoi An, 15 Nguyen Phuc Chu, Minh An Ward, Hoi An, Vietnam</li>\r\n<li>The LyLy Irish Pub &amp; Sports Bar Hoi An, 33 Nguyen Phuc Chu, Minh An Ward, Hoi An, Vietnam</li>\r\n<li>Madam Kieu Vietnamese Restaurant, 43 Nguyen Phuc Chu, Hoi An, Vietnam</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 id=\"3.7\">3.7 Great Place for Taking Photos.</h4>\r\n<p>The Night Market in Hoi An is a fantastic location for capturing memorable moments. The vibrant colors of the lanterns, the reflections on the river, and the lively atmosphere make for picturesque scenes. Don&rsquo;t forget to capture the unique architecture of Hoi An&rsquo;s Old Town.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"4\">4. How to Get to Hoi An Night Market?</h3>\r\n<h4 id=\"4.1\">4.1 From Hoi An.</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Walking or Bicycling:</strong>&nbsp;If you&rsquo;re staying within the central area of Hoi An, walking or cycling to the night market is a convenient option, especially if your accommodation is in the Old Town.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Electric Bus:</strong>&nbsp;if your hotel stays several km from the night market, then the electric bus will be the best option. Hotline: 0235 3 938 938</li>\r\n<li><strong>Private Transfer:</strong>&nbsp;If your hotel stays at Vinpearl Nam Hoi An, Blist Resort, or at An Bang Beach&hellip; you should take a private transfer from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/\">Hoiantravel</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 id=\"4.2\">4.2 From Da Nang.</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Taxi or Motorbike: These are readily available in Da Nang. It&rsquo;s about a 30-40 minute drive from Da Nang to Hoi An, depending on traffic. You should discuss the price with the driver first to start the trip.</li>\r\n<li>Private Transfer Services: There are various private transfer services, such as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmcar.com.vn/\">VMCar</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://danangdiscoveries.com/\">Da Nang Transfers</a>&nbsp;that offer transportation between Da Nang and Hoi An. These services often provide more comfort and the convenience of door-to-door service.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/team-vm-car.jpg\" alt=\"hoi an car rental\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"5\">5. Useful Tips for Hoi An Night Market.</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Go in the Evening:</strong>&nbsp;The night market comes to life in the evening, so plan your visit around sunset to fully enjoy the vibrant atmosphere and illuminated lanterns.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Cash is King:</strong>&nbsp;While some places might accept cards, it&rsquo;s advisable to carry cash for your purchases, especially in smaller stalls and markets.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Watch Your Belongings:</strong>&nbsp;As the market can get crowded, keep an eye on your belongings to prevent any potential issues with pickpocketing.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Try Local Foods:</strong>&nbsp;Don&rsquo;t miss the opportunity to indulge in Vietnamese street food. Be adventurous and try dishes like Cao Lau, Quang Noodles, and local specialties.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Suitable shoes:</strong>&nbsp;You should wear sports shoes or low-soled shoes and sandals, it will be more comfortable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 id=\"6\">6. The Hotel Near Hoi An Night Market</h3>\r\n<p>We highly recommend the hotels near the night market below:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cozy Savvy Boutique Hotel Hoi An, 116 Dao Duy Tu St, Cam Pho Ward, Hoi An, Quang Nam</li>\r\n<li>La Charm Hoi An Hotel &amp; Spa, 64 Dao Duy Tu St, Cam Pho Ward, Hoi An, Quang Nam</li>\r\n<li>Royal Riverside Hotel, 40 Nguyen Du St, Cam Pho Ward, Hoi An, Quang Nam</li>\r\n<li>Lantana Boutique Hoi An Hotel, 09 Thoai Ngoc Hau St, Minh An Ward, Hoi An, Quang Nam</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em>The Night Market in Hoi An is a must-visit destination in Vietnam, offering a unique blend of culture, cuisine, and shopping in a charming setting.</em></p>', 'posts/December2023/sOpY7P8x4QLwJ4NIkWFo.png', 'hoi-an-night-market-street-food-and-lots-of-shopping-2024', 'This place is known for its lively and festive atmosphere. You will see many beautifully lit up with colorful lanterns that add to the charm of the old town. It is a great time for relaxation in the riverside setting that enhances the experience. Let‚Äôs explore what to do in this night market right below.', 'Hoi An Night Market ‚Äì Street Food & Lots Of Shopping 2024', 'PUBLISHED', 1, '2023-12-28 21:18:30', '2024-01-17 02:25:24');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `author_id`, `category_id`, `title`, `seo_title`, `excerpt`, `body`, `image`, `slug`, `meta_description`, `meta_keywords`, `status`, `featured`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(19, 1, 1, 'Da Nang To Hoi An ‚Äì The Most Detailed Guide For Your Trip', 'Da Nang To Hoi An ‚Äì The Most Detailed Guide For Your Trip', 'Visitors can combine excursions to various tourist attractions from Da Nang to Hoi An. So, how many kilometers separate Da Nang and Hoi An? In truth, the distance between Da Nang and Hoi An is only approximately 30 kilometers, or 40 to 50 minutes by car. Visitors can easily have pleasure and amusement in both of these locations on the same trip.', '<h3 id=\"1\">1. Da Nang to Hoi An distance</h3>\r\n<p>The distance between Da Nang and Hoi An is not too far, and there are numerous ways to get there. There are four main routes from Da Nang to Hoi An that most travelers take:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Route 1</strong>&nbsp;is the quickest and most direct route, covering a distance of 28 kilometers from Da Nang&rsquo;s center to Hoi An. This route takes you through Da Nang&rsquo;s busiest streets, along Vo Nguyen Giap and Hai Ba Trung streets, before arriving in Hoi An.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Route 2</strong>&nbsp;is slightly longer (27 kilometers), taking you through National Road 1A, Vinh Dien Street, and Huynh Thuc Khang Street before arriving in Hoi An. This route is pleasant and provides views of the countryside.</li>\r\n<li><strong>The third route</strong>&nbsp;is the longest. The distance from Da Nang to Hoi An via this route is 30 kilometers, running from the city of Da Nang to Hoi An. It will take you across the province road of Da Nang before arriving in Hoi An. This path is ideal for individuals who want to explore Da Nang&rsquo;s suburbs.</li>\r\n<li><strong>The shortest route is route 4</strong>. The distance from Da Nang to Hoi An by this route is 25.4 kilometers. Before arriving at Hoi An, you will pass by Nguyen Tri Phuong Bridge, Vo Chi Cong Street, Tran Hung Dao, or Nguyen Tat Thanh Street. This route is ideal for people who want to escape Da Nang&rsquo;s congested streets and get to Hoi An as quickly as possible.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-at-night.jpg\" alt=\"hoi an night markets\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"2\">2. How to get from Da Nang to Hoi An</h3>\r\n<p>We have just introduced to you the routes you can take to get to Hoi An from Da Nang. But it seems like you are considering which type of means of transportation to choose so that you can also enjoy the beautiful scenery of the country along the way. Then we hope how to get from Da Nang to Hoi An will be useful to you.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.1\">2.1 Da Nang to Hoi An tour</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Private Tour:</strong>&nbsp;If you are traveling from Da Nang to Hoi An with a party of 1 to 8 people and have not planned ahead of time, the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/tours/day-trip-to-hoi-an-from-da-nang/\"><strong>Day Trip To Hoi An From Da Nang</strong></a>&nbsp;is for you. We will provide a minivan to serve you and keep you from being bothered. Furthermore, you do not need to worry about meals or tickets to sites on the itinerary because we have pre-arranged everything for the excursion.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Group Tour:</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/tours/day-trip-from-da-nang-to-hoi-an/\"><strong>Day Trip From Da Nang To Hoi An &ndash; Deluxe Group Tour</strong></a>, like the private tour, will include similar services such as a private car for your party, a local tour guide, entrance tickets to sights, and so on. However, it will only serve groups of 1 to 12 persons here; for bigger groups, please contact VM Travel for appropriate services.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>In general, both Private Tours and Group Tours provide the same services. Visitors should calculate the number of members as well as the appropriate finances to choose which type of service to use. If you have any questions, please contact&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/\">Hoi An Travel</a>, and our staff will answer them immediately!</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/things-to-do-in-hoian.jpg\" alt=\"How to get from Da Nang to Hoi An\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.2\">2.2 Getting Hoi An by private car</h4>\r\n<p>You can go from Da Nang to Hoi An by private car if you want quiet and lots of time to rest without being bothered. You won&rsquo;t have to worry about how many kilometers between Da Nang and Hoi An if you rent a car. If you are traveling with a group or family but are unfamiliar with the roads and want to travel comfortably, a vehicle rental service is the best option. Rental fees vary depending on the type of vehicle. 4.5-seat automobiles typically cost 500 to 600 thousand VND daily, whereas 7-seat autos cost 700 thousand VND to 1 million VND daily. If you book a Da Nang to Hoi An Tour of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://danangdiscoveries.com/danang-car-rental/\"><strong>Da Nang Car Rental</strong></a>, you will be accompanied by a local driver tour guide.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/da-nang-to-hoi-an-1.jpg\" alt=\"Hoi An from Da Nang by private car\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.3\">2.3 Getting Hoi An by grab &amp; taxi</h4>\r\n<p>A grab and taxi is the quickest and most convenient way to get from Da Nang to Hoi An. How long does it take to get from Da Nang to Hoi An by taxi? It just takes around 40 to 50 minutes to go to Hoi An, depending on traffic conditions. Visitors to Da Nang and Hoi An can simply discover cabs or order Grabs via the app. The cab fare from Da Nang to Hoi An, on the other hand, is quite steep, ranging from 350,000 VND to 430,000 VND one way or from 750,000 VND to 950,000 VND round trip. As a result, before utilizing this type of vehicle, tourists should examine whether it fits their budget for the entire trip.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.4\">2.4 Da Nang to Hoi An by motorbike</h4>\r\n<p>In addition to the options listed above, guests can travel from Da Nang to Hoi An by motorbike. This will be a genuinely fascinating experience for you. Visitors will be entirely proactive and can explore other tourist spots along the road if they ride a motorbike alone. Renting a scooter from Da Nang to Hoi An is also quite reasonable, costing between 120,000 and 200,000 VND per motorbike.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"2.5\">2.5 Da Nang to Hoi An by bus</h4>\r\n<p>The Da Nang to Hoi An by bus is probably the cheapest mode of transportation (about 30.000 VND per trip). Not only that, but the bus offers numerous excursions with varying time frames throughout the day (1 trip every 20 minutes), with hours of operation ranging from 5:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. daily. The disadvantage of this mode of transportation is that it takes a long time to travel, approximately 70-80 minutes. The bus only stops at predetermined locations and does not always take a direct route to your preferred location in Hoi An. However, if you want to visit the city in comfort, this is not a bad plan.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"3\">3. Da Nang Airport to Hoi An</h3>\r\n<p>The distance between Da Nang Airport and Hoi An is only about 30 kilometers. It just takes around 60 minutes to reach there by vehicle or motorcycle. Many tourists combine journeys to Hoi An and Da Nang during their trip because of the convenience of geographical distance.</p>\r\n<p>There are currently two main travel routes from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://danangdiscoveries.com/tour/transfer-da-nang-to-hoi-an/\"><strong>Da Nang airport to Hoi An</strong></a>, the fastest of which you can choose</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Route 1:</strong>&nbsp;departs from Da Nang city center (Da Nang airport is also in the city center region) and travels directly to the Vo Nguyen Giap/Lac Long Quan route. Then take the first right onto Hai Ba Trung Street. Continue straight along Ly Thai To Street to get to Hoi An.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Route 2:</strong>&nbsp;Begin on Nguyen Huu Tho street, proceed to the end of Nguyen Chi Con street, and then turn right at the roundabout into Tran Dai Nghia street. Continue straight on Nguyen Tat Thanh street, then turn right onto Ly Thuong Kiet street until you reach the end of the road to Hoi An ancient town (this path is faster, but you must be careful to avoid being confused).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/da-nang-airort-to-hoi-an.jpg\" alt=\"Da Nang Airport to Hoi An\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"4\">4. What to do in Hoi An?</h3>\r\n<p>Hoi An is a peaceful city with many lovely landscapes and locations for travelers to enjoy themselves and learn about the local culture. Let&rsquo;s visit areas that will help you better understand and appreciate the land and people of Hoi An!</p>\r\n<p><em>If you want to know more places to explore and visit in Hoi An, you can go to the article&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/things-to-do-in-hoian/\"><strong>Things to Do in Hoi An</strong></a>&nbsp;to access more information!</em></p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-at-night.jpg\" alt=\"What to do in Hoi An\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"4.1\">4.1 Visit Hoi An Ancient Town</h4>\r\n<p>For many domestic and foreign friends, visiting Hoi An Ancient Town is an interesting and memorable experience. Hoi An has a serene and old beauty; there is no noise or hustle. The antique architecture, moss-roofed cottages, bright lantern streets, and other features of the more than 400-year-old city add to its allure. You may not only immerse yourself in the beautiful beauty of the old town, but you can also explore the interaction of Eastern civilizations from Japan, China, and Vietnamese culture by visiting Hoi An ancient town. Because Hoi An was originally the busiest trading port that existed under the Nguyen Dynasty about 200 years ago, it was the trade between Vietnam and other countries (Japan, China, etc.) that created the multicultural and colorful Hoi An that exists to this day.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/walking-hoi-an-ancient-town.jpg\" alt=\"Visit Hoi An Ancient Town\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"4.2\">4.2 Explore snorkeling Cham Island</h4>\r\n<p>Cu Lao Cham is an island in Tan Hiep commune, Hoi An city. This place has quickly become an attractive destination for domestic and foreign tourists because of the peaceful beauty of the blue sea, white sand, and fresh, cool air. Explore snorkeling Cham Island has become a hot spot for coral diving services, attracting a large number of visitors to experience it. Being able to see and touch the beautiful, full-color coral pieces under the ocean is definitely an emotional and unforgettable experience for visitors. Therefore, even if you set foot on the green island without participating in the coral diving service on Cu Lao Cham island, your trip will lose all of its excitement!</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/cham-island-1.jpg\" alt=\"snorkeling Cham Island\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"4.3\">4.3 Take a boat Cam Thanh Coconut Village</h4>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/hoian-coconut-village/\"><strong>Cam Thanh Coconut Village</strong></a>, commonly known as the Bay Mau coconut forest, is a well-known ecotourism destination in Hoi An. Coming here, you will get the opportunity to ride a basket boat through a lush green coconut forest in a tranquil setting, watch basket dance performances, and boat races, and eat local specialties. This is a well-known tourist spot. Visit Hoi An as part of your Hoi An itinerary. This location offers you with a variety of unique and exciting experiences.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-coconut-village.jpg\" alt=\"Take a boat Cam Thanh Coconut Village\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"4.4\">4.4 Explore My Son Sanctuary</h4>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/my-son-sanctuary/\"><strong>My Son Sanctuary</strong></a>&nbsp;is a well-known historical site in Quang Nam Province, featuring an architectural complex of numerous exceptionally unusual Champa temples. This temple is regarded as one of Southeast Asia&rsquo;s top 10 most beautiful and well-known structures. This is also a sacred site that draws a lot of tourists. My Son Sanctuary will undoubtedly capture guests upon their first visit due to its unusual and long-standing architecture as well as a sense of mystery. In addition to admiring architectural works of outstanding creative value and discovering the significance of My Son Sanctuary, I had the opportunity to investigate the Cham people&rsquo;s cultural beauty.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/My-Son-Sanctuary-1.jpg\" alt=\"Explore My Son Sanctuary\"></div>\r\n<h4 id=\"4.5\">4.5 Experience Hoi An Lantern Festival</h4>\r\n<p>When traveling to Hoi An Ancient Town, visitors certainly cannot miss the colorful Hoi An Lantern Festival with beautiful, bright little lights floating lazily on the romantic Hoai River. This is a scene that everyone wants to see every time they have the opportunity to visit this ancient city. On these days, Hoi An&rsquo;s streets become sparkling and magical, with hundreds of lanterns hanging high. Visitors will be able to release small, colorful flower lanterns into the water by themselves, creating a very romantic scene. Hoi An Lantern Festival leaves a deep impression in the hearts of tourists from far and wide. That&rsquo;s when the ancient town becomes brilliant under the lights and buzzes with good luck wishes on the full moon night.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/best-time-to-visit-Hoi-An.jpg\" alt=\"Hoi An Lantern Festival\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"5\">5. Best time to visit Hoi An?</h3>\r\n<p>So what is the best time to visit Hoi An? This is a common question we get from travelers when they plan their trip to Hoi An. Hoi An&rsquo;s weather is typical of the Central Coast climate: hot and humid, with plenty of rain but also plenty of sunshine. However, because it is less influenced by the winter mist, it is less cold than other areas. There are two different seasons in the climate: rainy season and dry season.</p>\r\n<p>According to individuals who have visited Da Nang and Hoi An, the best time to visit is from February to April each year. It&rsquo;s early summer; it&rsquo;s not pouring terribly, and it&rsquo;s not too hot. The sun is dry and fresh, which is convenient for traveling, sightseeing, and admiring the beautiful scenery of Hoi An</p>\r\n<p>If you enjoy swimming in the summer, you can go between May and August. Summer is here, which means it&rsquo;s hot. You must use extreme caution to avoid headaches and heatstroke. There is a lot of rain in October and November, so it is only appropriate for relaxing and enjoying cuisine. A advice is to go on the 1st, 14th, or 15th day of the lunar calendar, especially when the old town is highly busy and dynamic at night.</p>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoian-countryside.jpg\" alt=\"Best time to visit Hoi An?\"></div>\r\n<h3 id=\"6\">6. Some Tips for Travelers When Transferring to Hoi An from Da Nang</h3>\r\n<p>To help passengers have the safest and most secure travel experience possible, we&rsquo;d like to offer the following tips when traveling from Da Nang to Hoi An:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Check travel times before departure:</strong>&nbsp;You should pay attention to travel time to avoid traveling during rush hours, which affects the journey. In addition, avoid traveling on holidays because this is the time when people are off work and they will take their families out, so pay attention to making arrangements that are convenient for yourself.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Prepare identification documents:</strong>&nbsp;Remember to prepare personal documents such as a passport, a citizen identification card, and a driver&rsquo;s license (if riding a motorcycle). The authorities will fine you if you do not bring it with you.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Strictly comply with traffic laws:</strong>&nbsp;It is necessary to comply with road traffic laws, allowed speeds on each route, and signs, especially when riding a motorcycle.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Note about the weather:</strong>&nbsp;You should also monitor the weather situation at the departure point as well as the destination to be fully prepared for the trip, and you should also prepare bags to carry your belongings if you travel in bad weather.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"tour-img\"><img src=\"https://hoiantravel.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/hoi-an-river-lantern.jpg\" alt=\"Tips for Travelers When Transferring from Da Nang to Hoi An\"></div>\r\n<p><em>In summary, there are many means of transportation from Da Nang to Hoi An for tourists to choose from. Based on your financial conditions, needs, and personal preferences, choose the most suitable vehicle. If you are interested in the information&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vmtravel.com/\"><strong>VM Travel &ndash; Vietnam Package Tours</strong></a>&nbsp;provided in the article and want to book a tour from Da Nang to Hoi An, please contact us below.</em></p>', 'posts/December2023/hUmraVpH6utJWDXdL9vu.png', 'da-nang-to-hoi-an-the-most-detailed-guide-for-your-trip', 'Visitors can combine excursions to various tourist attractions from Da Nang to Hoi An. So, how many kilometers separate Da Nang and Hoi An? In truth, the distance between Da Nang and Hoi An is only approximately 30 kilometers, or 40 to 50 minutes by car. Visitors can easily have pleasure and amusement in both of these locations on the same trip.', 'Da Nang To Hoi An ‚Äì The Most Detailed Guide For Your Trip', 'PUBLISHED', 0, '2023-12-28 21:19:34', '2023-12-28 21:19:34');

